components.content: On or after the following dates:

components.html:
You've received the largest amount possible for your school term

  • All your school costs may not be covered
  • You cannot appeal the amount
  • You may need to seek more funds outside StudentAidBC

components.html:
• Total family income on the previous year's returns:
    • Includes the income of your spouse, parents, stepparents, sponsors, or legal guardians OR
    • On your application if no return was available
  • Scholarships and bursaries reported
  • Voluntary or targeted contributions reported, and
  • Assets reported by parents, stepparents, sponsors, or legal guardians (dependent students only)
components.label: Content

components.html:
• If your school is to receive all or part of your funding, the amount you receive may be less than shown. Check with your school for more information.
  • We may not award you a loan if you:
    • Defaulted on previous student loans, or
    • Had funding restrictions added
components.label: Content

components.title: If you're not receiving new funds
components.label: If you're not receiving new funds

components.html:
Ask your school for a Confirmation of Enrolment (Schedule 2) if:

  • You're not receiving new funding, and
  • You're a full-time student, and
  • You want your loan to continue interest-free while you're in school

Submit the confirmation to the National Student Loans Service Centre. It must be received on or before the date you return to school.
components.label: Content

components.html:
The National Student Loans Service Centre (NSLSC) will email you instructions for creating an online account. 

  • This is where you'll submit your master student financial assistance agreement (MSFAA).

Create your account and then complete and submit your MSFAA.

  • Your 10-digit MSFAA number is XXXXXXXXXX

Once you've submitted your MSFAA, we'll deposit your loan to your account.
components.label: Content

components.title: If you've had a previous loan:
components.label: If you've had a previous loan:

components.html:
• You don’t need to submit an MSFAA
  • If needed, update your information with the National Student Loans Service Centre.
    • If your information isn’t correct, you may not receive your loan.
